# Hyacinth Haven: Houseplant E-Commerce Site

A hyacinth-themed e-commerce web application for selling unique houseplants, built with React and Redux. Features include a landing page, product listing with categories, a shopping cart, and responsive design.

## Features
- Landing page with company branding and call-to-action.
- Product listing with 6 hyacinth-inspired houseplants, grouped by categories (Spring Bloomers, Fragrant Favorites, Easy Care).
- Shopping cart with add/remove/update functionality.
- Header with navigation and live cart count.
- Themed with hyacinth colors (purples and pinks) for a floral, elegant feel.

## Technologies Used
- React (for UI components)
- Redux (for state management)
- React Router (for navigation)
- CSS (for styling)

## Installation and Setup
1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/Chunyunibyou/hyacinth-houseplants.git`
2. Navigate to the project directory: `cd hyacinth-houseplants`
3. Install dependencies: `npm install`
4. Start the development server: `npm start`
5. Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.

## Usage
- Browse plants on the product listing page.
- Add items to the cart (buttons disable after adding).
- View and manage cart on the shopping cart page.
- Navigate between pages using the header.

## Deployment
Deployed via GitHub Pages: [Live Site Link](https://Chunyunibyou.github.io/hyacinth-houseplants) (update if needed).

